title: Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set
description: When setting a filter like 'row[0] equals to 0' or when attempting to return a null result set, incorrect data set results are being returned.
OB: When an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set or when attempting to return a null result set, no relevant error message pops up.
EB: When an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set or when attempting to return a null result set, a relevant error message should pop up.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Set a filter expression like 'row[0] equals to 0' or attempt to return a null result set
2. Observe that incorrect data set results are returned
3. Check that no relevant error message pops up
